{"id": "EUVD-2022-54573", "enisaUuid": "acce45b4-be57-39a9-92db-759930c8e9fb", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncan: m_can: m_can_{read_fifo,echo_tx_event}(): shift timestamp to full 32 bits\n\nIn commit 1be37d3b0414 (\"can: m_can: fix periph RX path: use\nrx-offload to ensure skbs are sent from softirq context\") the RX path\nfor peripheral devices was switched to RX-offload.\n\nReceived CAN frames are pushed to RX-offload together with a\ntimestamp. RX-offload is designed to handle overflows of the timestamp\ncorrectly, if 32 bit timestamps are provided.\n\nThe timestamps of m_can core are only 16 bits wide. So this patch\nshifts them to full 32 bit before passing them to RX-offload.", "datePublished": "2025-10-22T18:30:32", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-22T18:30:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c7333f79888497bfd75dcd02a94eaf836dd1042c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2a2914a5bd7f38efe55a8372178146de82e0bce9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4c3333693f07313f5f0145a922f14a7d3c0f4f21", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49659"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49659"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0b394bec-095c-39e8-b9d1-d08a73132194", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.13"}, {"id": "68ddfcc5-14f2-3659-96c0-7f9721fe300c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.11"}, {"id": "76ad2f24-0f4b-307b-91a0-758cd5e55a76", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "90f7f0ab-afd8-3735-a507-fd765afff478", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1be37d3b0414e3db47f6fcba6c16286bbae0cb65 <4c3333693f07313f5f0145a922f14a7d3c0f4f21"}, {"id": "9ad77a55-509e-34d2-8584-48a313c17699", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1be37d3b0414e3db47f6fcba6c16286bbae0cb65 <c7333f79888497bfd75dcd02a94eaf836dd1042c"}, {"id": "a0d6fdec-3731-333b-8618-1ccb174c157c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}